openattic (2.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release.
  * Add dependencies to memcached and python-memcache.
  * Add check_volume_utilization and check_pool_utilization commands to nagios
    plugin config, install check_oa_utilization plugin.
  * Add system customization variables to /etc/default/openattic.
  * Rename the database to just "openattic".
  * Add dependency to python-django-rest-framework-bulk.
  * Reconfigure mod_wsgi to use processes instead of threads to avoid segfaults.
  * Add new openattic-auth-kerberos package to avoid asking confusing Kerberos
    questions unnecessarily during the installation.
  * Drop dependency on lio-utils.
  * Remove libnss-pgsql stuff (obsolete).
  * Add dummy openattic_contacts.cfg to ensure nagios can restart before this
    file has been overwritten by oA.
  * Add dependency to sg3-utils for disk detection.
  * Install serverstats.wsgi, adapt Apache config.
  * Remove openattic-module-{t,}ftp packages (support dropped upstream).
  * Drop dependency to libjs-extjs and oxygen-icon-theme.
  * Remove Apache Alias directives no longer needed for the new GUI.

